text:
HOLY SHIT!!

This movie has no reason to be as good as it is. I don’t remember enjoying a studio comedy this much in a long time. I would compare this more closely to Knives Out than a traditional studio comedy.

Part of the reason it is so fun is because it plays with your expectations the whole way through. Whether it’s who’s game it really is, or glass tables never breaking, and a number of other visual gags, when…
